                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Front View with Attachment Points</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Switch Installation</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Refer to the Figure below.</para>
            <para>If there is available switch capacity in location one, install the fog light control switch in
                location one. If the location one switch pack module is fully populated, install a six pack (part number
                3549776C4) in location two. Additional switch blanks (part number 3533950C1) may be needed to cover
                unused switch locations.
            </para>
            <figure id="f7300065" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/g73000a9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Control Panel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>Location 1: Six pack</callout1>
                    <callout1>Location 2: Six Pack</callout1>
                    <callout1>Location 3: Twelve Pack</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Wiring Fog Lights</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Refer to the Circuit Diagram Manual S08322, Chapter 9, Lights, Fog Light and Work Light for circuit
                installations.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Programming Fog Lights</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Adding fog lights will require reprogramming the system controller. See local dealer.</para>
